# MiladyOS init script.
#
# Lands at /product/etc/init/init.milady.rc and is loaded by init at
# boot. Use this for boot-time properties and service definitions
# that the privapp-permissions whitelist + default-permissions XML
# cannot express on their own.
#
# Reference: https://source.android.com/docs/core/init/init-language
#
# Property naming: do NOT prefix with `ro.` for properties that need
# to change across boot phases. AOSP makes `ro.*` immutable after the
# first set, so re-setting `ro.miladyos.boot_phase` at each phase
# silently fails with "Read-only property was already set". Use a
# non-`ro.` prefix (`miladyos.*`) for mutable boot markers.
#
# Appops grants: the JS-layer MiladyBootReceiver reflectively grants
# GET_USAGE_STATS (and any future appops) at sys.boot_completed time.
# Init.rc would need a custom SELinux service domain to fork sh, and
# Java reflection in the priv-app context is the simpler escape hatch.

on early-init
    setprop miladyos.boot_phase early-init

on init
    setprop miladyos.boot_phase init

on post-fs-data
    # Ensure the Milady process has writable scratch directory regardless
    # of which volume the user-data partition lands on. mkdir is idempotent.
    mkdir /data/milady 0770 system system

on boot
    setprop miladyos.boot_phase boot

on property:sys.boot_completed=1
    setprop miladyos.boot_phase completed
